result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Paul E. Dearborn was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:59 AM case called.  Defendant Paul E. Dearborn in court, in custody with attorney Annamarie A. Wineke.   Gilbert T. Thompson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Court reviewed CPR and PQWOR and heard heard plea of No Contest to OWI-5th as charged in the Information.  Ct. found plea given FKVI, accepted plea, and found Def guilty OWI-5th.  Based upon that plea, Count 2 of the Information is dismissed.  Court found factual basis in the Crim. Compl./Info.  BAC was .164%.  The Court heard from State, Defense and Def. and sentenced him as follows:  

66 months Imposed and stayed in the the Wisconsin State Prison System: 36 months of IC and 36 months of ES consecutive to any other sentence previously imposed. 

3 years probation with conditions:  12 months in the DCJail with H/T, commencing immediately
 $600 fine plus court costs and the driver improvement surcharge, 
$26 blood draw fee (BD Community Hospital),
AODA assessment and followthru, 
Absolute sobriety, no bars, beer tents, etc., and no going on premises where alcohol is served-this includes private parties at residences. 
Enroll and participate in the VA in-patient treatment 
Is to take any medation prescribed for his mental illness
Driver's license revoked for 36 months and is subject to a 36 month order requiring the following-the defendant's operating priv. for the operation of Class D vehicles be restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an IIL device
Any vehicle in def's. name to be equipped with an IIL 
58 days of presentence credit
